Anybody know how to target menu item (children) attributes using hubl? Preferably from within the menu variable that the module provides if that's even possible:
Ex: {% menu id="{{ module.primary_nav }}" %}

I'm hoping to be able to modify nav item links based off a conditional

Running into an issue getting custom module data from one page to another. It's basically an "Our Team" style listing page that links to the individual bio pages. Using the drag and drop editor with custom modules for both.

What I'm using is a repeating page field to select the pages that I want listed. From there, I can grab the page title and page URL no problem. However, on those pages are custom modules. I'd like to also display that content in this listing.

Code for the basic premise is this:

```{% for item in module.team_members %}
   &lt;div class="item"&gt;
      {% set my_content = content_by_id(item) %}
      &lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="{{ my_content.absolute_url }}"&gt;{{ my_content.name }}&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
      {{ module.name_and_title }}
      {{ module.bio }}
   &lt;/div&gt;
{% endfor %}```
What do I need to do to get this to work?
